{"lemma":"رَقَبَةٌ","slug":"رَقَبَةٌ","root":"ر.ق.ب","root_slug":"ر-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَقَبَة","root":"رقب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16308"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"neck"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a slave","tags":["metonymically"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَقَبَ (raqaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَقَبَ (raqaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ra.qa.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16308","headword_ar":"رَقَبَةٌ","root":"rqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"base of the hinder part thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hinder part of the base of the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper part of the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAbN","text_ar":"رِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Msb, K) and [coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabN","text_ar":"رَقَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K) and [pl. of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroqubN","text_ar":"اَرْقُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabaAtN","text_ar":"رَقَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  By a synecdoche, it is applied to (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole person"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a human being: as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*anobuhu fiY raqabatihi","text_ar":"ذَنْبُهُ فِى رَقَبَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His sin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crime,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be on his"},{"kind":"text","text":"own"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"neck;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAth, TA.) [Hence also] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlA^amoru fiY riqaAbikumo","text_ar":"هٰذَا الاَمْرُ فِى رِقَابِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This affair is upon your own selves"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY raqabatika","text_ar":"فِى رَقَبَتِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon thine own self"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEotaqa A@ll~`hu raqabatahu","text_ar":"اَعْتَقَ ا@للّٰهُ رَقَبَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God emancipate him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka","text_ar":"لَكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAbuhun~a wamaA Ealayohin~a","text_ar":"رِقَابُهُنَّ وَمَا عَلَيْهِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a trad., relating to camels, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They themselves, and the burdens that are upon them, are thine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And [hence], in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lanaA riqaAbu AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"لَنَا رِقَابُ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To us belongs the land itself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Hence also, i. e. by a synecdoche, (IAth, Mgh, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, IAth, Mgh, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a captive:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAbN","text_ar":"رِقَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEotaqa raqabapF","text_ar":"اَعْتَقَ رَقَبَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He emancipated a slave, male"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fak~a raqabapF","text_ar":"فَكَّ رَقَبَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He released a slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a captive."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iqaAb","text_ar":"الرِّقَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur ix. 60 means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those slaves who have contracted with their owners for their freedom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Mgh, Msb, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riqaAbu AlmazaAwidi","text_ar":"رِقَابُ المَزَاوِدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The necks of provision-bags"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a nickname which was applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajam","text_ar":"عَجَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persians,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foreigners"},{"kind":"text","text":"in general]; because they were red; (S, A;) or because of the length of their necks; (El-Karáfee, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zwd","text_ar":"زود"},{"kind":"text","text":";) or rather because of the thickness thereof, as though they were full. (MF in that art.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K","JK","S","TA","Msb","IAar","IAth","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}